Knab was founded in 2012 because we wanted to do things differently. Simpler, smarter and more advantageous for our customers. Because we believe we can help everyone maximize their financial affairs. "Feel at ease when it comes to your finances. Every day." By combining smart technical solutions with a healthy dose of human intelligence, we create financial services that really meet your needs. Add to that some of the sublime personal service from our employees and you end up with something that is truly unique to the world of finance! 
In a nutshell As Manager Digital Channels you’re responsible for the development of skills & capabilities of the digital channel specialists. In addition, you challenge the specialists in getting the most out of our digital channels which includes Search advertising, Display advertising, Social, SEO, Measurement, Direct Messaging, Public website & Notifications.   The team The expert center consists of several digital channel specialists a product owner and developers. In the HR Management line, 6 digital channels specialists and the PO digital channels report to the Manager Digital Channels. In this role you report directly to the CEO, Nadine Klokke. The developers that you are functionally responsible for (via the PO Digital Channels) report to the IT Chapter Lead.  
The Role Being an owner of an Expert Center means that you are responsible for the “How” and “What”. This means you will focus on the development of your team but also define what you will deliver with the team to make the most impact. The expert center supports several teams (e.g. commercial, brand, lending and more). The focus of the team will be in line with the OKR’s that we define on Knab level. To be successful in this role it is important you’re passionate about digital marketing channels and people development.  To be successful, 

You coach and empower your colleagues to take initiatives and propose solutions. You coach on hard & soft skills; 
Your team supports several teams, and you make sure they are enabled to deliver the best results but also challenge the priorities and demands from the organization; 
You have an outside perspective; what are the trends, what do we need to focus on, how do we handle changes within the industry that impact your field of work. By doing so, you make sure we stay ahead on development of the digital channels. 

Your Profile There is no predefined route to become our Manager Digital Channels, but this is the kind of profile we have in mind: 

You have 10+ years of experience in an e-commerce environment or a digital marketing agency; 
You have 3+ years of managerial/coaching experience; 
You have a background in several expertise’s within the scope of digital channels (e.g. Search advertising, display advertising, direct messaging, SEO, measurement, the public website & notifications); 
You are an inspiring leader and enjoy sharing your knowledge with the team; 
You are data driven and customer focused and love to collaborate with different people to get the most out of digital channels and are strong in stakeholder management; 
You are passionate about digital marketing channels and always look at how to get the most out of them; 
Verbally and written fluent in Dutch. 

Diversity Statement: Come as you are. Knab is an open workplace with positive vibes. We are inclusive of all nationalities, races and genders. We feel comfortable to bring our authentic whole selves to work and like you to do so too. 
Work with us! If you come to work with us, Knab will become a significant part of your life. Therefore, we make sure the ambiance is just as exciting as your job. Check the benefits! 
If you have any questions regarding this role or the process, please feel free to reach out to us! 
We don`t collaborate with third parties to fulfill this role.
